reviewText: I absolutely love Brush Strokes, and Karl Howman. Karl Howman was later in Mulberry Days, and he's just as good in Brush Strokes. If you like English comedy, you should see this.  NOTE: I HAVE A DVD PLAYER THAT WILL PLAY "PAL" DVD'S - YOU NEED ONE THAT WILL PLAY "PAL" TO PLAY BRUSH STROKES.
